race.comment: This race has been decimated by scratchings with the top few all coming out. It leaves MARBLE POINT (2) as the most likely winner, resuming for her second campaign. She won on debut at big odds in town, solid next time out before contesting a strong BM70 and struggling. She's got a bit of upside and strikes a very winnable race. TWISTED QUEEN (7) is another lightly raced type, second up off a pipe opener at Mornington. She finished at the rear there but will be better for it and should be a sharp improver. TIPSY GYPSY (6) is having her fourth run of her first campaign, winning her maiden two back before a trying effort on testing ground last time. She can improve again and should set up well here. LAVENDER GLORY (4) perhaps next best on better ground than she found last time.
